1 Planning for Gypsy and Traveller sites
The government’s planning policy for Traveller sites (first published in 2012,
last updated December 2023) sets out national planning policies for Gypsies
and Travellers.1 Local planning authorities (LPAs) must take the policy into
account in preparing their local plans. It is also a ‘material consideration’ in
planning decisions.2
In the policy, the government states that its “overarching aim” is to “ensure
fair and equal treatment” of Gypsies and Travellers and to facilitate their
“traditional and nomadic way of life [...] while respecting the interests of the
settled community”.3

Planning is a devolved matter, and this briefing focuses on England.
