General principles
In allocating land for Gypsy and Traveller sites and setting out local policies
that should be considered in decision-making, the government’s planning
policy for Traveller sites advises LPAs that they should consider how they can:
• ensure that Gypsy and Traveller sites are “sustainable economically,
socially and environmentally”.
• promote the “peaceful and integrated co-existence between the site and
the local community”.
• ensure that children living on the site can attend school on a regular
basis and promote access to health services, while avoiding placing
undue pressure on local infrastructure and service.
• protect local amenity and the local environment.10
